Figure 7. Induction of autophagy by hit compounds. Images of transgenic animals expressing Pnhx-2mCherry::lgg-1 treated with various compounds are shown. Images were acquired using a Nikon instruments TiEclipse widefield light microscope fitted with a 206 Plan Apochromat objective. Images were deconvolved using Volocity (Perkin Elmer, v 5.3.2). Deconvolved z planes were merged to a single plane. Well-fed animals treated with (A) DMSO show a diffuse mCherry expression throughout the intestine. In contrast, animals treated with (B) cantharidin, (C) fluphenazine and (D) pimozide show a markedly punctate distribution pattern indicative of increased autophagic activity. (E) Starved animals are included as a positive control for autophagy. Scale bar, 50 mm. doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0015460.g007

