Figure S1 Effect of fluphenazine on mCherry aggregation. To determine whether fluphenazine causes non-specific aggregation of mCherry, transgenic animals expressing Pnhx-2UbM::mCherry were exposed to fluphenazine for 24 hours. The UbM::mCherry fusion is used as a control for ubiquitin (Ub) fusion protein degradation. Upon Ub cleavage, the absence of a degradation signal (due to an N-terminal methionine) prevents mCherry degradation. Thus, mCherry behaves as an unmodified cytosolic protein [69]. Pnhx-2mCherry::lgg-1 (top) and Pnhx-2Ub(GM):: mCherry (bottom) animals were treated with (A, C) 0.5% DMSO or (B, D) 50 mM fluphenazine. Images were acquired using a Nikon instruments TiEclipse widefield light microscope fitted with a 406 objective. Scale bar, 100 mm. (JPG)

